Barclays Capital Reports Ashmore Group PLC (LON:ASHM) Upgrade, Express Scripts Holding Company (ESRX) Sellers Decreased By 5.25% Their Shorts


					
						July 20, 2017 - By Louis Casey

 Ashmore Group PLC (LON:ASHM)‘s old rating is no longer valid. Barclays Capital upped Ashmore Group PLC (LON:ASHM)‘s rating to a “Equal weight”.







 Express Scripts Holding Company (NASDAQ:ESRX) had a decrease of 5.25% in short interest. ESRX’s SI was 35.67 million shares in July as released by FINRA. Its down 5.25% from 37.64M shares previously. With 3.66M avg volume, 10 days are for Express Scripts Holding Company (NASDAQ:ESRX)’s short sellers to cover ESRX’s short positions. The stock decreased 0.96% or $0.6 during the last trading session, reaching $62.05. About shares traded. Express Scripts Holding Company (NASDAQ:ESRX) has declined 16.92% since July 20, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 33.62% the S&P500.
 About 89,047 shares traded. Ashmore Group plc (LON:ASHM) has 0.00% since July 20, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.
Ashmore Group plc is a United Kingdom company, which operates as a specialist emerging markets asset manager. The company has market cap of 2.58 billion GBP. The Firm offers a range of investment themes, such as external debt, local currency, corporate debt, blended debt, equities, alternatives, multi-strategy and overlay/liquidity. It has a 14.3 P/E ratio. The Company’s geographical divisions include United Kingdom, United States and Others.
Among 19 analysts covering Ashmore Group PLC (LON:ASHM), 4 have Buy rating, 5 Sell and 10 Hold. Therefore 21% are positive. Ashmore Group PLC has GBX 440 highest and GBX 181 lowest target. GBX 332.83’s average target is -8.79% below currents GBX 364.9 stock price. Ashmore Group PLC had 174 analyst reports since July 29, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The company was maintained on Friday, January 6 by Citigroup. The stock of Ashmore Group plc (LON:ASHM) earned “Underweight” rating by JP Morgan on Tuesday, January 17. The firm earned “Hold” rating on Monday, April 10 by Jefferies. JP Morgan maintained Ashmore Group plc (LON:ASHM) rating on Wednesday, September 7. JP Morgan has “Underweight” rating and GBX 250 target. Macquarie Research maintained it with “Neutral” rating and GBX 304 target in Monday, October 17 report. Barclays Capital maintained it with “Underweight” rating and GBX 250 target in Thursday, July 21 report. Peel Hunt upgraded Ashmore Group plc (LON:ASHM) rating on Monday, June 19. Peel Hunt has “Add” rating and GBX 400 target. The company was downgraded on Tuesday, April 19 by Peel Hunt. The firm has “Equal-Weight” rating given on Wednesday, November 25 by Morgan Stanley. The rating was maintained by BNP Paribas with “Neutral” on Thursday, March 10.








